  {
    "hotel_id": "2071358",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/cordis-shanghai-hongqiao/hotel/shanghai-cn.html",
    "name": "Cordis Shanghai Hongqiao",
    "detail": "Great hotel at good price for its quality. It's very close to Hongqiao Airport T2 and Hongqiao Train Station. You can walk to both from the hotel but be aware it's not signed well and few locals in the area speak English to ask directions! If you are flying into T1, it is quite challenging getting to T2. There is a Metro line underneath (only one stop) but you have to fully leave airport to get it (they is no internal route inside the airport, which is somewhat unusual for an airport!). I was told there was a bus every 30 mins between terminals but I couldn't find it so ended up getting a taxi around the airport at a cost of RMB55. There is a shopping mall very close the the hotel called the HUB, which also has a food court in basement. Only other thing to point out is this whole area is quite new, so I had trouble getting taxi's back to the hotel as they didn't know where it was. make sure you have the address written clearly in Chinese, ideally with a map if you go out. ",
