    "name": "Shanghai Fish Inn East Nanjing Road",
    "detail": "I could only write this review based on the amount of time I spent in Shanghai, which was only about 8 hours. I booked 2 rooms online for my party of 5, and arrived very late at night. Not knowing much of the area, and starving after a long flight, all we wanted was food. The staff was very nice and informative and directed us to a restaurant serving hot pot on Nanjing Road, which was excellent. With our bellies filled and extremely tired, we got back to our rooms and were satisfied with the comfort and cleanliness of the tiny rooms. The beds were very comfy and gave me the best night's sleep which made us ready to travel another 14 hours home. I'm so glad I booked these rooms, even though it was a very short experience of Shanghai, the food, and their nice people.",
